FBIS3-27931 "dreas021__a94004" FBIS-EAS-94-021-A Document Type:Daily Report 1 February 1994 ANNEX Japan Hata Reacts to PKO Participation in Yugoslavia OW3101002894 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 Jan 94 Morning Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW3101002894 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] Tsutomu Hata, deputy prime minister and foreign minister, gave a news conference in his capacity as head of Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party] at the Diet building on 29 January. Touching on the question of Japan's sending personnel to the former Yugoslavia to participate in UN Peacekeeping Operations (PKO), Hata said: "From an official standpoint, the overall situation has not met with the five principles on PKO participation (such as a cease-fire accord) yet. We will have to clarify this point." Thus, he indicated his view that the current situation in the former Yugoslavia does not fulfill the five principles.
